    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) and **Gleyber Torres** (67.46) anchor our lineup, benefiting significantly from soft matchups against Buehler and Hall respectively. **Freeman** is our highest-rated start; while his raw projections are modest, the combination of a high-park-factor environment and a favorable matchup against a pitcher with a slow delivery provides an elite environment for potential stolen base production\u2014a critical KPI for our roster. **Torres** is equally well-positioned, utilizing a strong platoon advantage against the left-handed Hall, while **Wenceel Perez** (66.02) rounds out our offensive core by leveraging similar platoon-driven efficiency to maximize our output in a hitter-friendly context.\n\nDespite his status as an anchor, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (54.47) presents a classic \"start your studs\" dilemma. His score is depressed by a difficult matchup against Lambert, who\u2014despite a pedestrian xERA\u2014is limiting production efficiency today. The most difficult bench decision involved **Matt Chapman** (46.10), who narrowly missed the cut. While **Chapman** was considered for the UTIL spot, the model favored the high-floor, platoon-advantaged **Gleyber Torres** to optimize our AVG and R categories. We are also monitoring the matchup for **Luis Arraez** (46.48) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (49.77); both face elite arms in Ohtani and Kay, respectively. While these players are essential to our core strategy, their scores reflect the high probability of a \"muted\" day given the quality of the opposing pitching. Ensure you track the confirmed lineups for **Jonathan Aranda** and **Jeremiah Jackson**, as their platoon utility is contingent on remaining in their projected slots.",
